state.unicode: Liberation will give rise to a new protectorate in the region, loyal to your nation whilst diplomatic relations are strong.
Resources permitting, a force of conscripts will be granted to the liberating army on behalf of the new protectorate.

uientry.s:
local this = UIComponent(Address) local parent = UIComponent(this:Parent("settlement_captured"))
function EmbeddedOnMouseLClickUp() parent :LuaCall("LiberateSettlement") end

state.unicode: Feeling neutral||This is the higher class public order.||Your higher class are currently neither angry nor happy.||Applying a little extra repression will improve their public order.||This is based on the positive and negative factors to the right.
Under control||This is the higher class public order.||Your higher class are currently under control.||This is based on the positive and negative factors to the right.

Angry||This is the higher class public order.||Your higher class are angry and are likely to cause trouble!||Try to placate the protesting populace by exempting the region from tax or increasing repression!||This is based on the positive and negative factors to the right.

Feeling neutral||This is the lowest class public order.||Your lowest class are currently neither angry nor happy.||They could go either way at the moment - improving repression a little will improve their public order.||This is based on the factors to the right.

Under control||This is the lowest class public order.||Your lowest class are currently under control.||They are either very happy, very repressed or a little of both!||This is based on the factors to the right.

Angry||This is the lowest class public order.||Your lowest class are currently angry and likely to riot.||Try increasing repression or exempting this region from tax to prevent rioting!||This is based on the factors to the right.
Peaceful occupation will result in minor damage to military buildings within the settlement.

uientry.s:
local this = UIComponent(Address) local parent = UIComponent(this:Parent("settlement_captured"))
function EmbeddedOnMouseLClickUp() parent :LuaCall("OccupySettlement") end
